HEADWORD: Lumbal
<hw>Lum"bal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>lumbus</ets> loin. See
<er>Loin</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or
near, the loins; <as>as, the <ex>lumbar</ex> arteries</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Lumbar region</b></col> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>, <cd>the
region of the loin; specifically, a region between the hypochondriac and
iliac regions, and outside of the umbilical region.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lumber</ent>⟦br⟧
